post_text:
SHC FAMILIES REGARDING PASSWORDS:
The district has purchased many new devices for the students through the Cares money due to COVID. In doing so, all the passwords have been reset for students. The accounts need to sync with the new devices through the school network. Therefore, students will need to login to their new devices at school to change their passwords so this happens. GROUP 2: Your first day assignments will be posted on your teachers’ websites (which you can access on phones, tablets or any device that is connected to internet or data. Go to shcsd.org, STAFF DIRECTORY, click on the teacher‘s name. These assignments can be done paper/pencil and will not require their Google Account. Once they get to school, passwords will be set and they will be ready to go.

post_text:
FALL SPORTS PHYSICAL INFORMATION

Football
Friday July 10
8:30-10:00 for grades 11-12
10:00-11:30 for grades 9-10
11:30-2:00 for grades 7-8

Monday July 13
8:30-10:00 Field Hockey and Soccer
10:00-12:00 Cheerleading grades 9-12
12:00-2:00 Cheerleading grades 7-8

Physical forms MUST be completed and signed in all appropriate places by parent/guardian BEFORE showing up for physical. Forms may be printed or picked up at the school.

If there are multiple siblings, they may all come on the same day, even if one is a football player and one is a field hockey player or cheerleader.

If you are sick, do NOT come to the school for a physical.

If you are not able to come to the school on either July 10 or July 13, notify your coach. You may also get a physical on your own with your own family doctor.

You must have a physical before you can participate in any organized practice with your team.

Forms can be printed below:
http://hsms.shcsd.org/apps/events/2020/7/10/8180997/?REC_ID=8180997&id=0

post_text:
COVID-19 COMMUNICATION UPDATE:

**SPECIAL NOTE: THERE HAVE BEEN NO CONFIRMED COVID-19 CASES WITHIN THE BOUNDARIES OF THE SHCSD AND THERE ARE NO PLANS TO CLOSE AT THIS TIME.

In the event of a positive COVID-19 confirmation within the boundaries of our school district, SHCSD will close.

The length of time will be determined based on collaboration and advisement from health care agencies.

PDE requires that any days missed for COVID-19 will fall under the same makeup requirements as inclement weather.

Due to the many unknowns, please understand that the direction and information that the district receives can change from day-to-day or possibly hour-by-hour.

Cleanliness and sanitation remain a top priority for our maintenance staff and all district employees.

Come out and support a GREAT cause tonight at the SHC Lady Rockets Pink Game. Their will be raffle baskets, 50/50, Chuck the Duck, Pink Hot Shot, food, etc. The Lady Rockets will be donating all proceeds go to Women's Imaging Center in Huntingdon.

The Women's Imaging Center will be collecting hand sanitizer and hand lotions to distribute to cancer patients.

The players will be honoring special people in their lives who have had cancer. They will be walking with cancer survivors and family members of those who have lost the fight during the evening. The Jr High walk will begin at approximately 4:30 and the JV/Varsity walk will be after the Jr. High game. We look forward to seeing everyone there tonight to support this great cause!

text: Today it was reported to the administration that a high school student allegedly made a threat involving a weapon. Following an administrative investigation, the report is unfounded. The Pennsylvania State Police have been notified.

post_text: Following lunch today a rumor was circulating within the high school about a student having or bringing a gun to school. The administration interviewed many students and acquired statements and this alarm was unfounded. A conversation between two students was taken completely out of context. This rumor was never a threat to the safety of the school and the administration is confident the issue has been resolved.
